d46adbf8-218a-40f1-83c7-c1ed74486e82.do_description: To make the output, you have to...fill the black area within the gray with red if it is a square; otherwise, leave it alone.
d46adbf8-218a-40f1-83c7-c1ed74486e82.grid_description: The output grid size...should be the same as the input
d46adbf8-218a-40f1-83c7-c1ed74486e82.see_description: In the input, you should see...gray objects with the black area inside.

e9356cae-e272-49c5-b40d-9f73c3795823.do_description: To make the output, you have to...fill in the holes with orange that are perfect squares only. Do not fill in rectangles or L shapes
e9356cae-e272-49c5-b40d-9f73c3795823.grid_description: The output grid size...same size and gray objects are in the same position so just copy the input over
e9356cae-e272-49c5-b40d-9f73c3795823.see_description: In the input, you should see...gray objects in a black area

ed57b166-8a91-4c3d-a9bf-6defddaf67ce.do_description: To make the output, you have to...color the center point of the grey box with orange
ed57b166-8a91-4c3d-a9bf-6defddaf67ce.grid_description: The output grid size...remain the same, the grid size did not change at all
ed57b166-8a91-4c3d-a9bf-6defddaf67ce.see_description: In the input, you should see...gray fill of different size with block grids inside

f7d924d0-4fd8-410d-a528-209de7b060f9.do_description: To make the output, you have to... if the big gray squares have a perfect black square within it, color it red. Perfect squares are such as 1x1, 2x2, 3x3.
f7d924d0-4fd8-410d-a528-209de7b060f9.grid_description: The output grid size... remains the same as input
f7d924d0-4fd8-410d-a528-209de7b060f9.see_description: In the input, you should see... big gray squares with some black spaces inside
